141548/http://cashboxmagazine.com/archives/70s_files/1970YESP.html |archivedate= 22 September 2012}}. [[Cashbox (magazine)|''Cash Box'' magazine]].</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|35\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Certifications==\n{{Certification Table Top}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United Kingdom|type=single|artist=Mungo Jerry|title=In the Summertime|award=Silver|relyear=2005|certyear=2020|accessdate=27 March 2020}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United States|type=single|artist=Mungo Jerry|title=In the Summertime|award=Gold|relyear=1970|certyear=1970|accessdate=11 October 2019}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom|nosales=true|streaming=true}}\n\n==Shaggy version==\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = In the Summertime\n| cover      = In the Summertime single.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Shaggy (musician)|Shaggy]] featuring [[Rayvon]]\n| album      = [[Boombastic (album)|Boombastic]] {{no italic|and}} Flipper Soundtrack\n| B-side     = {{unbulleted list|\"It No Matter\"|\"Gal You a Pepper\"}}\n| released   = 1995\n| format     = {{hlist|[[CD single]]|[[Cassette single|cassette]]|[[12-inch single|12\" vinyl]]}}\n| recorded   = 1995<br/>1996 (re-recorded)\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Reggae]]<ref>{{cite magazine|first= Fred |last= Bronson |title= All-Time Hottest Songs of Summer |magazine= [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |date= 30 July 2005 |volume= 117 |issue= 31 |page= 34 |issn= 0006-2510 |url= https://books.google.com/?id=oRQEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA34}}</ref>\n| length     = 3:46\n| label      = [[Virgin Records|Virgin]]\n| writer     = [[Ray Dorset]]\n| producer   = Shaggy, Rayvon\n| chronology = [[Shaggy (musician)|Shaggy]]\n| prev_title = Lately\n| prev_year  = 1994\n| next_title = [[Boombastic (song)|Boombastic]]\n| next_year  = 1995\n| misc       = {{Extra album cover\n | header  = \"In the Summertime\" ('96 Version)\n | type    = single\n | cover   = In the Summertime 96 Version Shaggy.png\n | border  =\n | alt     =\n | caption = Single cover for the re-recorded version\n}}\n}}\n\nIn 1995, Jamaican-American rapper [[Shaggy (musician)|Shaggy]] covered the song, and released it as the lead single from his third studio album, ''[[Boombastic (album)|Boombastic]]''.<ref>{{cite magazine|first= Havelock |last= Nelson |title= An Early 'Summertime' from Shaggy |magazine= [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |date= 29 April 1995 |volume= 107 |issue= 17 |page= 16 |issn= 0006-2510 |url= https://books.google.com/?id=5AsEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA16&lpg=PA16}}</ref> Aside from the addition of rap lyrics, Shaggy's version also substitutes other lyrics for the song's original line containing \"have a drink, have a drive.\" Shaggy also performed the song on an episode of ''[[Baywatch]]''.<ref>{{cite|first= Carrie |last= Witmer |title= All the stars you had no idea were once on 'Baywatch' |magazine= Business Insider |date= 26 May 2017 |accessdate= 18 June 2017 |url= http://www.businessinsider.com/people-who-were-on-baywatch-2017-5}}</ref> A year after its release, the song was re-recorded and released specifically for the film ''[[Flipper (1996 film)|Flipper]]'' under the title \"In the Summertime\" ('96 Version).\n\n===Track listing===\n; United Kingdom\n* '''CD single'''<ref>{{cite web|title= Shaggy \u2013 In The Summertime (CD) |publisher= [[Discogs]] |accessdate= 4 August 2013 |url= http://www.discogs.com/Shaggy-In-The-Summertime/release/558874}}</ref>\n# \"In the Summertime\" (Single Edit) \u2013 3:46\n# \"It No Matter\" \u2013 3:56\n# \"Gal You A Pepper\" \u2013 3:37\n# \"In the Summertime\" (Sting vs. Shaggy Remix) \u2013 4:40\n\n* '''7\" vinyl / Cassette'''<ref>{{cite web|title= Shaggy \u2013 In The Summertime (Vinyl) |publisher= Discogs |accessdate= 4 August 2013 |url= http://www.discogs.com/Shaggy-In-The-Summertime/release/555828}}</ref>\n# \"In the Summertime\" (Single Edit) \u2013 3:46\n# \"It No Matter\" \u2013 3:56\n\n* '''12\" vinyl'''<ref>{{cite web|title= Shaggy Feat. Rayvon \u2013 In The Summertime (Vinyl) |publisher= Discogs |accessdate= 4 August 2013 |url= http://www.discogs.com/Shaggy-Feat-Rayvon-In-The-Summertime/release/1405753}}</ref>\n# \"In the Summertime\" (Sting vs. Shaggy Remix) \u2013 4:40\n# \"In the Summertime\" (LP Version) \u2013 3:55\n# \"In the Summertime\" (Drum Dancehall Mix) \u2013 3:54\n\n* '''1996 \"Flipper\" CD single'''<ref>{{cite web|title= In the Summertime: Amazon.co.uk: Music |publisher= [[Amazon.com]] |accessdate= 4 August 2013 |url= https://www.amazon.co.uk/Summertime-Shaggy/dp/B00006ZSQX/ref=sr_1_1?s=music&ie=UTF8&qid=1327836409&sr=1-1}}</ref>\n# \"In the Summertime '96\" (Original Version) \u2013 3:52\n# \"In the Summertime '96\" (Instrumental) \u2013 3:52\n# \"Flipper Main Theme\" \u2013 3:58\n\n; United States\n* '''CD single'''<ref>{{cite web|title= Shaggy \u2013 In The Summertime / Boombastic (CD) |publisher= Discogs |accessdate= 4 August 2013 |url= http://www.discogs.com/Shaggy-In-The-Summertime-Boombastic/release/383692}}</ref>\n# \"In the Summertime\" (Single Edit) \u2013 3:48\n# \"In the Summertime\" (LP Version) \u2013 3:55\n# \"In the Summertime\" (Drum Dancehall Mix) \u2013 3:54\n# \"In the Summertime\" (Funk Dance Mix) \u2013 3:58\n# \"Boombastic\" (LP Version) \u2013 4:05\n# \"Boombastic\" (Sting Remix) \u2013 4:18\n\n* '''12\" vinyl'''<ref>{{cite web|title= Shaggy \u2013 In The Summertime / Boombastic (Vinyl) |publisher= Discogs |accessdate= 4 August 2013 |url= http://www.discogs.com/Shaggy-In-The-Summertime-Boombastic/release/1714350}}</ref>\n# \"In the Summertime\" (LP Version) \u2013 3:55\n# \"In the Summertime\" (Drum Dancehall Mix) \u2013 3:54\n# \"In the Summertime\" (Funk Dance Mix) \u2013 3:58\n# \"Boombastic\" (Sting Remix) \u2013 4:18\n\n===Charts===\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n====Weekly charts====\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Chart (1995)\n!Peak<br/>position\n|-\n{{singlechart|Australia|14|artist=Shaggy feat. Rayvon|song=In the Summertime|accessdate=19 January 2014}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Austria|35|artist=Shaggy feat. Rayvon|song=In the Summertime|accessdate=19 January 2014}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Flanders|32|artist=Shaggy feat. Rayvon|song=In the Summertime|accessdate=19 January 2014}}\n|-\n|Finland ([[Suomen virallinen lista]])<ref>{{cite book|first= Jake |last= Nyman |edition= 1st |year= 2005 |location= Helsinki |isbn= 951-31-2503-3 |title= Suomi soi 4: Suuri suomalainen listakirja |publisher= Tammi |language= fi}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|7\n|-\n{{singlechart|Germany2|60|artist=Shaggy feat. Rayvon|song=In the Summertime|songid=57855|accessdate=7 December 2016|refname=\"ShaggyGer\"}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Ireland2|13|song=In the Summertime|accessdate=2 June 2013}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Dutch40|23|artist=Shaggy Featuring Rayvo - In The Summertime|accessdate=19 January 2014}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Dutch100|21|artist=Shaggy feat. Rayvon|song=In the Summertime|accessdate=19 January 2014}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|New Zealand|4|artist=Shaggy feat. Rayvon|song=In the Summertime|accessdate=19 January 2014}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Sweden|30|artist=Shaggy feat. Rayvon|song=In the Summertime|accessdate=19 January 2014}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|UK|5|date=1995-07-22|artist=Shaggy feat. Rayvon|accessdate=19 January 2014}}\n|-\n|US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]]<ref name=\"awards\">{{cite web|url= http://www.allmusic.com/album/boombastic-mw0000173245/awards |title= Boombastic \u2013 Awards |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20160513085106/http://www.allmusic.com/album/boombastic-mw0000173245/awards |archivedate= 13 May 2016}}. [[AllMusic]]. [[All Media Network]].</ref>{{efn|name=doubleA}}\n|align=\"center\"|3\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' [[Dance/Electronic Singles Sales|Hot Dance Music/Maxi-Singles Sales]]<ref name=\"awards\"/>{{efn|name=doubleA}}\n|align=\"center\"|2\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs|Hot R&B Singles]]<ref name=\"awards\"/>{{efn|name=doubleA}}\n|align=\"center\"|1\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' [[Hot Rap Songs|Hot Rap Singles]]<ref name=\"awards\"/>{{efn|name=doubleA}}\n|align=\"center\"|1\n|-\n|US ''[[Cashbox (magazine)|Cash Box]]''<ref>{{cite magazine|title= CASH BOX Top 100 Pop Singles \u2013 Week ending AUGUST 26, 1995 |magazine= [[Cashbox (magazine)|Cash Box]] |url= http://cashboxmagazine.com/archives/90s_files/19950826.html |archivedate= 10 October 2012 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20121010231911/http://cashboxmagazine.com/archives/90s_files/19950826.html}}</ref>{{efn|name=doubleA}}\n|align=\"center\"|3\n|}\n{{col-2}}\n\n====Year-end charts====\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Chart (1995)\n!Rank\n|-\n|New Zealand ([[Recorded Music NZ]])<ref>{{cite web|title= End of Year Charts 1995 |publisher= [[Recorded Music NZ]] |accessdate= 3 December 2017 |url= http://nztop40.co.nz/chart/?chart=3884}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|21\n|-\n|US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]]<ref>{{cite web|title= Top 100 Hits for 1995 |publisher= The Longbored Surfer |url= http://longboredsurfer.com/charts/1995 |accessdate= 19 January 2014}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|18{{efn|name=doubleA}}\n|-\n|US [[Cashbox (magazine)|''Cash Box'']]<ref>{{cite magazine|title= The CASH BOX Year-End Charts: 1995 |magazine= [[Cashbox (magazine)|Cash Box]] |url= http://cashboxmagazine.com/archives/90s_files/1995YESP.html |archivedate= 10 October 2012 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20121010232426/http://cashboxmagazine.com/archives/90s_files/1995YESP.html}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|23{{efn|name=doubleA}}\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n{{notelist|refs=\n{{efn|name=doubleA|Charted as a [[double A-side]] with \"Boombastic\".}}\n}}\n\n===Certifications===\n{{Certification Table Top}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=New Zealand|type=single|artist=Shaggy|title=In the Summertime|award=Gold|relyear=1995|certyear=1995|id=3676|recent=website|accessdate=11 October 2019}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United Kingdom|type=single|artist=Shaggy ft Rayvon|title=In the Summertime|award=Silver|relyear=1995|certyear=2019|accessdate=11 October 2019}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom|noshipments=true|streaming=true}}\n\n==Other uses==\nThe song's lyric \"have a drink, have a drive, go out and see what you can find\" led to its use in a UK advert for the campaign [[Drinking and Driving Wrecks Lives]]. It featured the first verse against people enjoying drinks in a pub during summer, then stopped to show a fatal car accident caused by [[Driving under the influence|drink driving]].<ref>{{cite news|title= Summer drink-drive campaign launched |newspaper= [[The Independent]] |date= 22 June 1994 |accessdate= 2 May 2012 |url= https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/summer-drinkdrive-campaign-launched-1424254.html}}</ref><ref>{{YouTube|f5ma_Xv7rGM|\"Don't Drink & Drive - In The Summertime - UK Advert - 1992\"}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n*[[List of best-selling singles]]\n*[[List of Billboard number-one rap singles of the 1980s and 1990s#1995|List of ''Billboard'' number-one rap singles of the 1980s and 1990s]]\n*[[List of Dutch Top 40 number-one singles of 1970]]\n*[[List of number-one singles in Australia during the 1970s]]\n*[[List of number-one singles of 1970 (Canada)]]\n*[[List of number-one singles of 1970 (France)]]\n*[[List of number-one hits of 1970 (Germany)]]\n*[[List of number-one singles of 1970 (Ireland)]]\n*[[List of number-one hits of 1970 (Italy)]]\n*[[List of number-one singles in 1970 (New Zealand)]]\n*[[List of number-one singles of 1970 (Spain)]]\n*[[List of number-one singles from 1968 to 1979 (Switzerland)]]\n*[[List of number-one R&B singles of 1995 (U.S.)]]\n*[[List of UK Singles Chart number ones of the 1970s]]\n*[[VG-lista 1964 to 1994]]\n*[[List of one-hit wonders in the United States#1970s|List of 1970s one-hit wonders in the United States]]\n\n{{div col end}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{MetroLyrics song|mungo-jerry|in-the-summertime}}<!-- Licensed lyrics provider -->\n*{{YouTube|wvUQcnfwUUM|Mungo Jerry - In The Summertime ORIGINAL 1970}}\n\n{{Mungo Jerry}}\n{{Shaggy singles}}\n\n[[Category:1970 songs]]\n[[Category:1970 debut singles]]\n[[Category:1995 singles]]\n[[Category:Mungo Jerry songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Ray Dorset]]\n[[Category:Skiffle songs]]\n[[Category:Shaggy (musician) songs]]\n[[Category:Dawn Records singles]]\n[[Category:Pye Records singles]]\n[[Category:Virgin Records singles]]\n[[Category:Dutch Top 40 number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Single Top 100 number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Irish Singles Chart number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Australia]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Austria]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in France]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Germany]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Italy]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in New Zealand]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Norway]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in South Africa]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Switzerland]]\n[[Category:RPM Top Singles number-one singles]]\n[[Category:UK Singles Chart number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Ultratop 50 Singles (Flanders) number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Billboard Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Billboard Hot Rap Songs number-one singles]]\n", "text_old": "{{Other uses}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2014}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = In the Summertime\n| cover      = MungoJerryInTheSummertime7InchSingleCover.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Mungo Jerry]]\n| album      = [[Electronically Tested]]\n| B-side     = Mighty Man\n| released   = 1970\n| format     =\n| recorded   = {{unbulleted list|1970|Pye Recording Studios, [[Marble Arch]], London}}\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Skiffle]]<ref>{{cite news|first= Bill |last= Holdship |title= That summer feeling |newspaper= [[Metro Times]] |date= 17 June 2009 |url= http://www2.metrotimes.com/arts/story.asp?id=14086 |accessdate= 29 May 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|first= Moira |last= McCormick |title= Elfin's Listening-Post Towers Bring Children's Artists To Upscale Market |magazine= [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |date= 18 May 1996 |volume= 108 |issue= 20 |page= 50 |issn= 0006-2510 |url= https://books.google.com/?id=uA0EAAAAMBAJ&pg=RA1-PA50&dq=%22skiffle%22}}</ref>\n| length     = 3:40\n| label      = [[Dawn Records|Dawn]]\n| writer     = [[Ray Dorset]]\n| producer   = Barry Murray\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title = [[Baby Jump]]\n| next_year  = 1971\n| misc       = {{Audio sample\n | type        = single\n | file        = In the Summertime (Mungo Jerry song).ogg\n | description = \"In the Summerime\"\n}}\n}}\n\"'''In the Summertime'''\" is the debut single by British rock band [[Mungo Jerry]]. Written and composed by its lead singer, [[Ray Dorset]], it celebrates the carefree days of summer. In 1970, it reached number one in charts around the world, including seven weeks on the [[UK Singles Chart]], two weeks on one of the [[RPM (magazine)|Canadian charts]], and number three on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] singles chart in the US. It became one of the [[List of best-selling singles|best-selling singles of all-time]], eventually selling 30 million copies.<ref>{{cite web|first= Craig |last= Harris |title= Ray Dorset \u2013 Artist Biography |website= [[AllMusic]] |accessdate= 20 January 2019 |url= https://www.allmusic.com/artist/ray-dorset-mn0000345252/biography}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title= The essential summer mix |newspaper= [[The Guardian]] |date= 29 July 2006 |url= https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2006/jul/29/culturaltrips.pop}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|first= Laura |last= Nightingale |title= Mungo Jerry celebrates 45 years of In the Summertime at Camberley Theatre |newspaper= [[Surrey Advertiser|Get Surrey]] |date= 7 October 2015 |accessdate= 10 February 2019 |url= https://www.getsurrey.co.uk/whats-on/music-nightlife-news/mungo-jerry-celebrates-45-years-10201428}}</ref>\n\n==Background==\nDorset has said that the song only took ten minutes to write, which he did using a second-hand [[Fender Stratocaster]] while he was taking time off work from his regular job, working in a lab for [[Timex Group|Timex]].<ref>{{cite news|first= Peter |last= Robertson |title= Whatever happened to In The Summertime singer Mungo Jerry |newspaper= [[Daily Express]] |date= 26 April 2014 |accessdate= 9 July 2014 |url= http://www.express.co.uk/life-style/life/472160/Mungo-Jerry-sang-In-The-Summertime}}</ref>\n\nThe initial UK release was on [[Dawn Records]], a new label launched by [[Pye Records|Pye]]. It was unusual in that it was a [[maxi single]], playing at 33-1/3 rpm, whereas singles generally played at 45 rpm. It included an additional song also written and composed by Dorset, \"Mighty Man,\" on the A-side, and a much longer track, the [[Woody Guthrie]] song \"Dust Pneumonia Blues,\" on the B-side. As the record was sold in a picture sleeve, also not standard at the time, and only sold at a few pence more than the normal 45 rpm two-track single, it was considered value for money. A small quantity of 45 rpm discs on the Pye record label, with \"Mighty Man\" on the B-side, and without a picture sleeve, were pressed for use in [[jukebox]]es. These are now rare collector's items.\n\nIn 2012, Dorset sued his former management company Associated Music International, run by his former friend and business manager Eliot Cohen, claiming over \u00a32 million in [[royalties]] from the song that he believed had been withheld from him.<ref>{{cite web|title= Mungo Jerry Star Suing Over Alleged Unpaid Royalties |website= [[Contactmusic.com]] |date= 22 January 2012 |accessdate= 25 May 2014 |url= http://www.contactmusic.com/news/mungo-jerry-star-suing-over-alleged-unpaid-royalties_1285706}}</ref><!-- outcome unclear, so assuming out-of-court settlement with reporting restrictions-->\n\nIn an interview with Gary James, Dorset explained the origin of the \"motorcycle\" sound towards the false ending in the middle of the song: \"I said, 'We'll just get a recording of a motorcycle, stick it on the end of the song and then re-edit the front and then put the front off to the motorcycle so it starts up again.' But I couldn't find a motorcycle. Howard Barry, the engineer had an old, well, it wasn't old then, a [[Triumph Motor Company|Triumph]] sports car, which he drove past the studio while Barry Marrit was holding the microphone. So, he got the stereo effects from left to right or right to left, whatever. And that was it.\"<ref>{{cite interview|first= Ray |last= Dorset |interviewer= Gary James |title= Gary James' Interview With Ray Dorset Of Mungo Jerry |publisher= Classicbands.com |accessdate= 9 July 2014 |url= http://www.classicbands.com/MungoJerryInterview.html}}</ref>\n\n==Personnel==\nCredits adapted from the single [[liner notes]] for \"In the Summertime\".<ref>{{cite AV media notes|title= In the Summertime |others= Mungo Jerry |year= 1970 |url= https://www.discogs.com/release/1468468-In-The-Summertime/images |accessdate= 31 July 2017 |type= liner notes |publisher= [[Dawn Records|Dawn]]}}</ref>\n* [[Ray Dorset]] \u2013 [[lead vocalist|vocals]], [[electric guitar]], [[Acoustic guitar|6 string acoustic]], [[cabasa]], stomp\n* [[Paul King (Mungo Jerry)|Paul King]] \u2013 [[banjo]], [[Jug (instrument)|jug]]\n* Colin Earl \u2013 [[piano]]\n* Mike Cole \u2013 [[double bass|string bass]]\n\n==Charts==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Chart (1970)\n!Peak<br/>position\n|-\n|Australia ([[Go-Set|Go-Set National Top 40]])<ref>{{cite magazine|title= Go-Set Australian charts \u2013 29 August 1970 |magazine= [[Go-Set]] |accessdate= 4 August 2013 |url= http://www.poparchives.com.au/gosetcharts/1970/19700829.html}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|1\n|-\n|Australia ([[Kent Music Report]])<ref>{{cite web|title= Australia No. 1 hits -- 1970's |website= World Charts |accessdate= 19 January 2014 |url= http://www.worldcharts.co.uk/chartfeatures/aus/aus70.htm |url-status= dead |archi