k Radio]])<ref>{{cite web|title= South African Rock Lists Website SA Charts 1969 \u2013 1989 Acts (B) |publisher= Rock.co.za |url= http://www.rock.co.za/files/springbok_top_20_(B).html |accessdate= 29 January 2014}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|1\n|-\n|Spain ([[Productores de M\u00fasica de Espa\u00f1a|AFE]])<ref>{{cite book|first= Fernando |last= Salaverri |title= S\u00f3lo \u00e9xitos: a\u00f1o a a\u00f1o, 1959\u20132002 |edition= 1st |date= September 2005 |publisher= Fundaci\u00f3n Autor-SGAE |location= Spain |isbn= 84-8048-639-2 |language= es}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|1\n|-\n{{singlechart|Sweden|1|artist=Boney M.|song=Rivers Of Babylon|accessdate=29 January 2014}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Switzerland|1|artist=Boney M.|song=Rivers Of Babylon|accessdate=29 January 2014}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|UK|1|date=19780513|accessdate=29 January 2014}}\n|-\n|US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]]<ref>{{cite web|title= Nightflight to Venus \u2013 Awards |publisher= [[AllMusic]]. [[All Media Network]] |url= http://www.allmusic.com/album/nightflight-to-venus-mw0000527966/awards |accessdate= 29 January 2014}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|30\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' [[Adult Contemporary (chart)|Adult Contemporary]]<ref>{{cite book|first= Joel |last= Whitburn |authorlink= Joel Whitburn |year= 1993 |title= Top Adult Contemporary: 1961\u20131993 |publisher= Record Research |page= 31}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|35\n|-\n|US [[Cashbox (magazine)|''Cash Box'']]<ref>{{cite magazine|title= CASH BOX Top 100 Singles \u2013 Week ending AUGUST 5, 1978 |magazine= [[Cashbox (magazine)|Cash Box]] |url= http://cashboxmagazine.com/archives/70s_files/19780805.html |archivedate= 4 October 2012 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20121004181501/http://cashboxmagazine.com/archives/70s_files/19780805.html}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|54\n|}\n{{col-2}}\n\n====Year-end charts====\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Chart (1978)\n!Position\n|-\n|Australia ([[Kent Music Report]])<ref>{{cite web|title= Forum \u2013 ARIA Charts: Special Occasion Charts \u2013 Top 100 End of Year AMR Charts \u2013 1970s |url= http://australian-charts.com/forum.asp?todo=viewthread&id=40276 |publisher= Australian-charts.com. Hung Medien |accessdate= 29 January 2014 |url-status= dead |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20131106213449/http://australian-charts.com/forum.asp?todo=viewthread&id=40276 |archivedate= 6 November 2013}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|3\n|-\n|Austria ([[\u00d63 Austria Top 40]])<ref>{{cite web|title= Jahreshitparade 1978 |publisher= Austriancharts.at. Hung Medien |accessdate= 29 January 2014 |url= http://www.austriancharts.at/1978_single.asp |language= de}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|1\n|-\n|Belgium ([[Ultratop|Ultratop 50]] Flanders)<ref>{{cite web|title= Jaaroverzichten 1978 |publisher= [[Ultratop]]. Hung Medien |accessdate= 29 January 2014 |url= http://www.ultratop.be/nl/annual.asp?year=1978 |language= nl}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|3\n|-\n|France ([[Institut fran\u00e7ais d'opinion publique|IFOP]])<ref>{{cite web|title= TOP \u2013 1978 |publisher= Top-france.fr |accessdate= 29 January 2014 |url= http://www.top-france.fr/html/annuel/1978.htm |language= fr}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|7\n|-\n|Germany ([[GfK Entertainment|Media Control Charts]])<ref>{{cite web|title= Jahrescharts \u2013 1978 |publisher= Officialcharts.de. [[GfK Entertainment]] |url= http://www.officialcharts.de/year.asp?cat=s&country=de&year=1978&x=29&y=9 |archivedate= 16 December 2014 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20141216035013/http://www.officialcharts.de/year.asp?cat=s&country=de&year=1978&x=29&y=9 |language= de}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|2\n|-\n|Netherlands ([[Dutch Top 40]])<ref>{{cite web|title= Top 100-Jaaroverzicht van 1978 |publisher= [[Dutch Top 40]] |accessdate= 29 January 2014 |url= http://www.top40.nl/bijzondere-lijsten/top-100-jaaroverzichten/1978 |language= nl}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|3\n|-\n|Netherlands ([[Single Top 100]])<ref>{{cite web|url= http://dutchcharts.nl/jaaroverzichten.asp?year=1978&cat=s |title= Jaaroverzichten \u2013 Single 1978 |publisher= [[Single Top 100]]. Hung Medien |accessdate= 29 January 2014 |language= nl}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|1\n|-\n|New Zealand ([[Recorded Music NZ]])<ref>{{cite web|title= End of Year Charts 1978 |publisher= [[Recorded Music NZ]] |accessdate= 3 March 2020 |url= https://nztop40.co.nz/chart/index_chart?chart=3867}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|1\n|-\n|South Africa ([[Springbok Radio]])<ref>{{cite web|title= Top 20 Hit Singles of 1978 |url= http://www.rock.co.za/files/sahits_1978.html |publisher= Rock.co.za |accessdate= 29 January 2014}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|1\n|-\n|Switzerland ([[Swiss Hitparade|Schweizer Hitparade]])<ref>{{cite web|title= Schweizer Jahreshitparade 1978 |publisher= Hitparade.ch. Hung Medien |url= http://hitparade.ch/year.asp?key=1978 |accessdate= 29 January 2014 |language= de}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|1\n|-\n|UK Singles ([[UK Singles Chart|Official Charts Company]])<ref>{{cite web|first= Dan |last= Lane |title= The biggest selling singles of every year revealed! (1952-2011) |publisher= [[Official Charts Company]] |date= 18 November 2012 |url= http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/the-biggest-selling-singles-of-every-year-revealed-1952-2011-1720/ |accessdate= 29 January 2014}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|1\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n====Sales and certifications====\n{{Certification Table Top}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Austria|type=single|artist=Boney M.|title=Rivers of Babylon|nocert=true|salesamount=30,000|salesref=<ref>{{cite magazine|first= Manfred |last= Schreiber |title= From the Music Capitals of the World > Vienna |magazine= Billboard |page= 100 |date= 13 June 1978 |accessdate= 13 November 2019 |url= https://www.americanradiohistory.com/Archive-Billboard/70s/1978/Billboard%201978-06-03.pdf}}</ref>|relyear=1978}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Belgium|artist=Boney M.|title=Rivers of Babylon|nocert=yes|salesamount=200,000|salesref=<ref name=\"R&R\"/>}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=France|type=single|artist=Boney M.|title=Rivers of Babylon|award=Gold|certyear=1978|salesamount=1,070,000|salesref=<ref>{{cite web|title= InfoDisc : Tous les Titres par Artiste |url= http://www.infodisc.fr/S_Certif_Or.php?debut=64 |publisher= InfoDisc |accessdate= 29 March 2012 |language= fr}}</ref>|recent=false}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Germany|type=single|artist=Boney M|title=Rivers of Babylon|award=Platinum|relyear=1978|certyear=1978|salesamount=1,000,000|salesref=<ref name=\"R&R\">{{cite magazine|title= The Biggest River In The World Just Got Bigger |url= http://www.americanradiohistory.com/Archive-RandR/1970s/1978/RR-1978-06-23.pdf |magazine= [[Radio & Records]] |date= 23 June 1978 |page= 6 |accessdate= 26 July 2015}}</ref>}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Netherlands|artist=Boney M.|title=Rivers of Babylon|award=Gold|salesamount=300,000|certyear=1978|salesref=<ref name=\"R&R\"/>}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Switzerland|type=single|artist=Boney M.|title=Rivers of Babylon|nocert=true|salesamount=125,000|salesref=<ref>{{cite magazine|first= Pierre |last= Haesler |title= Ventriloquist LP Topping Swiss Charts |magazine= Billboard |page= 104 |date= 20 January 1979 |accessdate= 28 July 2019 |url= https://www.americanradiohistory.com/Archive-Billboard/70s/1979/Billboard%201979-01-20.pdf}}</ref>|relyear=1978}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United Kingdom|type=single|artist=Boney M|title=Rivers of Babylon|award=Platinum|certyear=1978|accessdate=29 March 2012|salesamount=2,032,656|salesref=<ref name=\"UK sales\">{{cite web|first= Rob |last= Copsey |title= The UK's Official Chart 'millionaires' revealed |publisher= [[Official Charts Company]] |date= 19 September 2017 |accessdate= 1 May 2019 |url= https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/the-uks-official-chart-millionaires-revealed__20459/}}</ref>}}\n{{Certification Table Summary}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|title=Rivers of Babylon|artist=Boney M|type=album|relyear=1978|region=Benelux|nocert=true|salesamount=638,000|salesref=<ref>{{cite magazine|first= Willem |last= Hoos |title= Promotion Ploys Intrigue Labels in Netherlands |magazine= Billboard |page= 94 |date= 20 January 1979 |accessdate= 13 July 2019 |url= https://books.google.com/books?id=JCUEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PT93&dq=638,000}}</ref>}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom}}\n{{col-end}}\n\n===1988 Remix===\n'''\"Rivers of Babylon\" / \"Mary's Boy Child\" / \"Oh My Lord\"''' was a 1988 [[remix]] single issued to launch the group's reunion. (Boney M. had split up in 1986, their 10th anniversary.) The double-A-side single contained new mixes of the band's two most successful single releases ever. Although the [[Greatest Hits of All Times \u2013 Remix '88|remix album]] from which both sides of the single were taken sold well, the single failed to chart.\n\n===Parody===\nThe song was parodied by [[The Barron Knights]] in their UK comedy hit \"A Taste of Aggro\" (1978), in which the lyrics are changed to \"There's a dentist in Birmingham, he fixed my crown / And as I slept, he filled my mouth with iron.\" The song was their biggest hit, reaching no. 3 in the UK charts.<ref>{{cite web|title= Barron Knights |publisher= Official Charts Company |url= http://www.officialcharts.com/artist/11192/BARRON%20KNIGHTS/ |accessdate= 9 May 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Other recorded versions==\nThe [[Unitarian Universalist Association]] has included the song in their supplemental hymnal ''Singing the Journey'' (Hymn #1042).<ref>{{cite web|title= Generated Recordings of Hymns For Educational Use |publisher= [[Unitarian Universalist Association]] |date= 25 October 2012 |accessdate= 14 April 2013 |url= http://www.uua.org/worship/music/hymnals/journey/52328.shtml}}</ref> On 19 November 1978, a [[cover version]] with lyrics in [[Swedish language|Swedish]], \"Kommer du ih\u00e5g Babylon?\" (\"Do you remember Babylon?\"), performed by [[Sweden|Swedish]] [[dansband]] [[Schytts]]<ref>{{cite web|url= http://smdb.kb.se/catalog/id/001555236 |title= Kommer du ih\u00e5g Babylon / Schytts |publisher= [[Svensk mediedatabas]] |accessdate= 29 January 2014 |language= sv}}</ref> entered the first place on [[Svensktoppen]].<ref>{{cite web|title= Svensktoppen \u2013 ''1978'' |publisher= Sveriges Radio |url= http://sverigesradio.se/Diverse/AppData/Isidor/files/2023/3476.txt |accessdate= 29 January 2014}}</ref> where it stayed for 10 weeks up to 14 January 1979.<ref>{{cite web|title= Svensktoppen \u2013 ''1979'' |url= http://sverigesradio.se/Diverse/AppData/Isidor/files/2023/3477.txt |publisher= Sveriges Radio |accessdate= 29 January 2014}}</ref>\n\n==In popular culture==\nOn 30 September 1979, \"Rivers of Babylon\" was sung by an estimated crowd of 280,000 people attending the papal visit of [[Pope John Paul II|John Paul II]] in [[Galway]] near [[Limerick]], [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]].<ref>{{cite news|title= Pope arrives for U.S. visit |date= 1 October 1979 |newspaper= [[The Kingman Daily Miner]] |url= https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=932&dat=19791001&id=LFALAAAAIBAJ&sjid=9VIDAAAAIBAJ&pg=6170,10162 |accessdate= 29 January 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.galwayraces.com/papal-visit-1979 |title= Papal Visit 30th September, 1979 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20090421201737/http://www.galwayraces.com/papal-visit-1979 |archivedate= 21 April 2009}}. [[Galway Races]].</ref>\n\nThe song features prominently in the 2009 Kazakh film ''[[Tulpan]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title= Tulpan (2008) |date= 13 March 2009 |publisher= Efareviews.cineuropa.org |url= http://efareviews.cineuropa.org/2009/03/tulpan-2008.html |accessdate= 29 January 2014}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*\"[[Va, pensiero]]\", story of Jewish exiles from Judea\n*[[List of best-selling singles in Germany]]\n*[[List of best-selling singles by year in the United Kingdom]]\n*[[List of Dutch Top 40 number-one singles of 1978]]\n*[[List of European number-one hits of 1978]]\n*[[List of number-one hits of 1978 (Germany)]]\n*[[List of numbe